---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../site.config";

const updatedAt = siteConfig.updatedAt;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="编辑准则 | 异环攻略站"
  description="异环攻略站编辑准则，说明内容来源、更新原则、纠错机制、广告独立性与版权处理方式。"
  jsonLd={{
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebPage",
    name: "编辑准则",
    dateModified: updatedAt
  }}
>
  <article class="prose lang-zh max-w-none">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-neon">Editorial Policy</p>
    <h1>编辑准则</h1>
    <p>最后更新日期：{updatedAt}</p>

    <p>
      本站希望为《异环》玩家提供可检索、可复查、可长期维护的中文攻略内容。为了避免误导读者，本站按以下准则编辑和更新页面。
    </p>

    <h2>1. 来源处理</h2>
    <p>
      攻略内容主要基于公开游戏资料、官方公告、站点编辑实测、社区反馈和版本更新后的整理。涉及推测、体验评价或阵容推荐时，页面会尽量使用“建议”“推荐”“适合”等表达，避免把主观判断写成绝对结论。
    </p>

    <h2>2. 人工复核</h2>
    <p>
      站点内容在发布前会尽量经过人工复核，重点检查标题、步骤顺序、路线描述、更新时间和引用是否一致。对依赖版本状态的内容，若无法从当前版本确认，就不会把它写成确定结论。
    </p>

    <h2>3. 更新原则</h2>
    <p>
      角色数值、技能描述、抽卡规则、任务流程和地图收集点可能随版本变化而调整。本站会优先更新影响玩家决策的内容，例如角色培养优先级、活动流程、材料路线和高价值奖励信息。
    </p>

    <h2>4. 纠错机制</h2>
    <p>
      如果页面存在错误、遗漏或版本过期信息，欢迎通过 <a href="/contact/">联系我们</a> 页面反馈。收到可核验信息后，本站会尽快修订，并在必要时补充说明或更新时间。
    </p>

    <h2>5. 广告独立性</h2>
    <p>
      本站可能通过 Google AdSense 等广告服务展示广告。广告收入不会影响攻略结论、角色评价或内容排序。若未来出现赞助、推广或合作内容，页面会明确标注，避免与普通攻略混淆。
    </p>

    <h2>6. 修订记录</h2>
    <p>
      对于重大版本更新、角色重做、地图重绘或工具逻辑变化，站点会优先更新对应页面的标题、正文和更新时间。必要时会在更新日志或页面正文中补充变更说明，帮助读者判断哪些结论已经过期。
    </p>

    <h2>7. 低价值内容处理</h2>
    <p>
      本站不会为了增加页面数量而发布只有标题、少量摘要、重复卡片或未完成占位内容的页面。列表页需要提供清晰导航和阅读说明，正文页需要包含可执行步骤、判断依据、常见误区、版本复查点或工具使用说明。
    </p>
    <p>
      如果某个页面内容过短、与其他页面高度重复、缺少原创整理，或只复制公告而没有补充解读，本站会优先选择扩写、合并到更完整的专题、从导航中移除，或暂缓发布到公开站点。对搜索页、联系页等功能页面，本站会补充使用说明和替代路径，避免用户进入后没有可用信息。
    </p>

    <h2>8. 版权处理</h2>
    <p>
      本站尊重游戏开发商、发行商、创作者和其他权利人的合法权益。若权利人认为本站内容涉及侵权或不当使用，请提供具体链接和权利证明，我们会在核实后及时处理。
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="prose lang-en max-w-none">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-neon">Editorial Policy</p>
    <h1>Editorial Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: {updatedAt}</p>

    <p>
      This site aims to provide searchable, reviewable and maintainable Neverness to Everness guide content. The following principles explain how pages are written, checked and updated.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Source Handling</h2>
    <p>
      Guides are based on public game information, official announcements, editorial testing, player feedback and post-update organization. When a recommendation is based on testing or judgment, we use language such as "recommended", "suitable" or "best for" instead of presenting subjective opinions as absolute facts.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Human Review</h2>
    <p>
      Pages are reviewed before publication where practical. We check titles, step order, route descriptions, update dates and source consistency. If version-dependent information cannot be confirmed, it is not written as a final conclusion.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Update Principles</h2>
    <p>
      Character values, skill text, pull rules, quest steps and map collectibles may change by version. We prioritize updates that affect player decisions, such as character investment, event routing, material farming and high-value rewards.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Corrections</h2>
    <p>
      Errors, missing details and outdated information can be reported through the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>. When feedback is verifiable, the relevant page is revised and its update date or notes may be adjusted.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Advertising Independence</h2>
    <p>
      This site may display Google AdSense or similar advertising. Ad revenue does not control guide conclusions, character evaluations or content order. Sponsored or promotional content, if added in the future, will be labeled clearly.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Revision Records</h2>
    <p>
      Major game updates, character reworks, map changes and tool-logic changes are reflected in page titles, body text and updated dates where relevant. Important changes may also be summarized in page notes or changelog entries.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Low-Value Content Handling</h2>
    <p>
      We do not publish pages only to increase page count. A page should not consist only of a title, a short summary, repeated cards or an unfinished placeholder. Index pages need clear navigation and reading context; article pages need steps, reasoning, mistakes to avoid, version review points or tool-use explanations.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pages that are too short, highly repetitive, copied without added analysis, or unsupported by original organization are expanded, merged into a stronger topic page, removed from navigation or delayed until they are useful. Functional pages such as search and contact include usage guidance and alternate paths so users are not left with an empty screen.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Copyright Handling</h2>
    <p>
      We respect the rights of developers, publishers, creators and other rights holders. If a rights holder believes content on this site is infringing or improperly used, they can provide the specific URL and rights documentation for review.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
